# vendor/ is committed on purpose — the action runs straight from a release
# tag's checkout, so the sandbox files must be in git. dist/ is NOT: the
# Release workflow builds it and layers it onto the release tag's commit
# (see .github/workflows/release.yml), so main stays TypeScript-only.
# Root-anchored: vendor/dist/ IS committed.
/dist/
node_modules
coverage
*.log

# IDE
.idea
.claude/*
CLAUDE.md